  "body": "You can use `>` to create a file with the output of the `flatten` task, but this is not discoverable for people that are not very familiar with the shell. Plus, AFAIK that doesn't work on Windows's cmd.\r\n\r\nWe should add a `--output` parameter with a path to the file that will be created.\r\n\r\n```\r\nhh flatten --output Flattened.sol\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf the file exists, it should be overriden.\r\n\r\nSee related discussion [here](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/issues/1049#issuecomment-733682350).",
